      "raw_text": "A Racine, Wis, judge yesterday\nawarded $4,000 damages to a\nbaker against the Racine Trades\nand Labor council on account of a\nboycott instituted by that body. The\ndecision received considerable at\ntention from union men here and\nover the country generally. Local\nunion men say that the decision\nwill be a good thing for labor as It\nshows that existing laws protect\nthe capitalist while labor receives\nlittle or no attention at the hands\n&C egi.lative bodies. being left\nwithout remedy against the black\nlist. Nothing could happen that\nwill aid Gompers labor campaign\nmore, so local union men say."
    }
  ]
